# here is how to use akshaytorch

# 

1. gelu -> it handles any shape you give , but for now i will take (B , C , H , W) , so our gelu will normalize with dim -1 as obvious

2. fused residual kernel ->  it takes two inputs the x and the residual and and normalized (layer norm) with respect to dim = -1, which is  optimized for diffusion , takes any shape 

3. matmul kernel -> takes any shape , matmul at last dims as per needed for diffusion 

4. Relu -> takes any shape , relu norm

5. concat and concatfused -> takes any shape and concat just concat and concat fused does concat along relu norm

